        "content": "<p>My paper on the use of Lean in High Energy Physics appeared on the arXiv today at:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.08863\">https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.08863</a></p>\n<p>In writing the paper I made some domain-specific choices. The most notably is the use of the word 'digitalisation', instead of `formalising'. This was done because the word \"formal\" means something else to the average high energy physicist.</p>",
        "id": 439004218,
        "sender_full_name": "Joseph Tooby-Smith",
        "timestamp": 1715861540
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A small comment: on page 8, the <code>![![x, y], ![z, 0]]</code> notation shouldn't be used for matrices; you should use <code>!![x, y; z, 0]</code> instead.</p>",
        "id": 439012929,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1715863864
